        "contentSnippet": "Journalistic texts come in many forms. Whether it’s a bold opinion editorial, an exciting sports article, or a cutting -edge science report—each one has a unique structure and style that serves a specific purpose and audience. In this activity, you will examine how these texts are built and how their features work together to communicate information clearly and effectively. Read the excerpts below focusing on each article’s type, purpose, and structural features. Article Excerpt A (Opinion Editorial):“We must hold public officials accountable. Corruption thrives in silence, and our voices are needed to push reforms…” Article Excerpt B (Sports Article):“The Tigers triumphed last night in a nail-biting 82-80 win against the Spartans. With only two seconds left, Reyes sank the winning shot…” Article Excerpt C (Science & Tech Article):“A breakthrough in solar panel efficiency could reshape the country’s energy sector, according to researchers at UP Diliman…” Excerpt Article Type Main Purpose Text Structure Features A. Opinion Editorial To persuade or argue a viewpoint Argumentative tone, thesis, supporting evidence, emotive appeal B. Sport Article To inform/ entertain about a game Chro"
