        "contentSnippet": "An expository essay is a type of informational text that explains, clarifies, or informs. Its clarity depends on how ideas are organized. The structure of an expository essay usually follows this pattern: ● Introduction (Thesis Statement) – tells readers the topic and main point. ● Body Paragraphs – each one focuses on a clear idea with supporting evidence, details, or examples. ● Conclusion – summarizes and reinforces the essay’s purpose. Exercise: Read the given expository excerpt and answer the questions that follow. 1. Which sentence shows the introduction? __________________________ 2. What are the main ideas in the body? List them.____________________ 3. Which part shows the conclusion?_________________________________ Dynamic Learning Program S.Y. 2025-2026 English 8 Q4-LAS-1 L E A R N I N G A C T I V I T Y S H E E T Name: Score: Grade & Section: Date: Type of Activity: (Check or choose from below.) □ Concept Notes □ Performance Task □ Formal Theme □ Others: □ Skills: Exercise / Drill □ Illustration □ Informal Theme Activity Title: Structure of an Expository Essay Learning Target: To identify the structure of an expository essay. References: (Author, Title, Pages) Formentera"
