        "contentSnippet": "Asian performing and visual arts are a reflection of rich cultural traditions and evolving innovations. Conventional techniques include long-practiced methods such as traditional costumes, symbolic hand gestures, live musical instruments, and ritual-based choreography. On the other hand, emerging techniques involve the use of modern technology such as digital sound effects, projection mapping, LED lighting, and multimedia installations. The blending of these techniques shows how Asian arts preserve cultural identity while adapting to contemporary creativity. Learning Activity / Task: Watch a short video clip of a Balinese dance performance and a contemporary Asian digital art installation. Make a list of at least: x Three conventional techniques (e.g., hand gestures, costumes, live instruments). x Three emerging techniques (e.g., projection mapping, digital sound effects, and LED displays). Guide Questions: 1. What traditional elements did you notice in the Balinese dance (e.g., costumes, gestures, music)? 2. How did these elements reflect cultural identity or tradition? 3. What modern or emerging techniques did you see in the digital art installation? 4. In your opinion, how can t"
