        "downloadUrl": "https://drive.google.com/uc?id=1oB-eseFMs9qQnRZZMqZwKtuAM9pgU7D2&export=download",
        "contentSnippet": "Research is a systematic process of collecting and analyzing information to discover solutions to a problem. It follows a certain method or structure to analyze data. There are two specific types of research: (1) applied , a scientific study that seeks to solve practical problems; and (2) basic or pure research, an inquiry driven by scientific curiosity in scientific investigation. There are also language features in research that researchers should familiarize themselves such as: Terms Definition Data is factual information used to make informed decisions. Design is the strategy for answering the research questions. Statistics is the organization and study of numerical data. Survey is a research tool used to gather information about a topic. Treatment is the course of action designed for research. Exercise: Identify the research term and its definition used in the paragraph below. In research, the background of the study explains a brief history as to why the topic is being conducted, focusing on the challenges and results of the current studies. Dynamic Learning Program S.Y. 2025-2026 English 10 Q2-LAS - 01 L E A R N I N G A C T I V I T Y S H E E T Name: Score: Grade & Section: D"
