        "contentSnippet": "An academic text is a kind of reading material that contributes to study and practice in a specific field, industry, or course. Academic texts are research papers, manuals, guides, and textbooks on particular disciplines. In research, identifying terminologies is the bas ic step in the research work. Identifying and defining these technical terms will lead you to successful research. Technical terms are essential in academic texts because they allow for precision, clarity, and conciseness within a specific field of study. Technical terms must be defined to establish precision and clarity, conciseness, and credibility. Technical terms in research may be grouped as: a. Research basic terms: literature, theory, and variables b. Research hypotheses: null, rival, and testing hypothesis c. Research population and sampling : stratified, random, snowball, purposive d. Research data: nominal, ordinal, interval, ratio Exercise: Arrange the jumbled letters to reveal the technical terms described. 1. ASRBTATC A concise summary of a research paper. 2. HTPSETSHIYO A testable statement or prediction about the relationship between two or more variables. 3. YETDOHMDOLG The systematic approach and s"
