        "contentSnippet": "Engaging with the Concept of Creativity What comes to your mind when you hear the word creativity? Write your answers using the following bubble map. Activity: “Creative Moments” Think about a time you felt particularly creative, whether it was in school, at home, or with friends. What were you doing? What made it feel creative? Write your answers in a clean sheet of paper. Have you noticed that creativity is not just about art. It can be about problem-solving, innovation, and expressing yourself in unique ways. Introducing the Creative Economy Now let us zoom out a bit. All that creative energy and creative outputs have economic value. That is where the “creative economy” comes in. It refers to economic activities that rely on creative talent, skills, and intellectual property to produce goods and services with cultural, artistic, or entertainment value. Key Characteristics of the Creative Economy The creative economy is fundamentally driven by intangible assets, where intellectual property like copyright, trademarks, and patents hold significant value. It heavily relies on human capital, the unique skills and talent of individuals as its primary resource. This sector possesses a "
